      "role": "user",
      "content": "i'm having a nightmare with an embedded project for a car ECU. it's C++ and we have this slow memory leak that only shows up after like 4 or 5 hours of steady state operation. i can't find where the allocation isn't being freed. \n\nhere is the main telemetry loop:\n\nvoid process_sensor_data(SensorPacket* packet) {\n    if (packet->status == VALID) {\n        DataLog* log = new DataLog(packet->payload);\n        log_store->push_back(log);\n        \n        if (log_store->size() > MAX_LOG_SIZE) {\n            // we should be cleaning up here but i can't track it down\n            log_store->remove_oldest(); \n        }\n    }\n}\n\ncan you help me figure out a systematic way to track down exactly where this leak is happening? i can't use heavy tools like Valgrind because of the hardware constraints.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
